The S&P 500 is regarded as a gauge of the large cap U.S. equities
market. The index includes 500 leading companies in leading industries
of the U.S. economy, which are publicly held on either the NYSE or
NASDAQ, and covers 75% of U.S. equities. Since this is a price index
and not a total return index, the S&P 500 index here does not contain
dividends.
